In this press gaggle, White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs provides updates on various topics. He mentions positive feedback on the Afghanistan/Pakistan review process and strategy, Iran's attendance at a regional conference, and the President's conversation with Prime Minister Brown. Gibbs also discusses the upcoming meeting with Russian President Medvedev and addresses concerns about North Korea's threat to start a war. He emphasizes the importance of productive relationships with Russia and China and discusses the measures that will likely be agreed upon at the G20 summit, including addressing the global recession and implementing stronger financial regulations. Gibbs mentions progress in discussions with NATO and highlights the significance of Iran's involvement in addressing concerns in Afghanistan. Finally, he briefly mentions the special election in New York's 20th congressional district.